org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.portsandflows

Interface ItemFlow

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ItemFlowImpl

    public interface ItemFlow
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Item Flow'. An ItemFlow describes the flow of items across a connector or an association. It may constrain the item exchange between blocks, block usages, or flow ports as specified by their flow properties. For example, a pump connected to a tank: the pump has an “out” flow property of type Liquid and the tank has an “in” FlowProperty of type Liquid. To signify that only water flows between the pump and the tank, we can specify an ItemFlow of type Water on the connector.

    The following features are supported:

    • Base Information Flow
    • Item Property
    See Also:
    PortsandflowsPackage.getItemFlow()

      • getItemProperty

        org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property getItemProperty()
        Returns the value of the 'Item Property' reference. An optional property that relates the flowing item to the instances of the connector’s enclosing block. This property is applicable only for item flows assigned to connectors. The multiplicity is zero if the item flow is assigned to an Association.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Item Property' reference.
